---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-15", modifiedDate: "2026-03-28", section: "City Guides" };
const topics = ["city", "market"];
---

<Layout 
  title="Lewiston Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Lewiston, Maine cannabis dispensary guide. Navigate the second-largest city market with insights on local ordinances and business opportunities."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  article={article}
  topics={["city", "market"]}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Lewiston Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Lewiston, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>📋 Lewiston at a Glance</h2>
      <table aria-label="Lewiston dispensary requirements and market data" caption="Key requirements and market data for opening a dispensary in Lewiston">
        <thead><tr><th scope="col">Requirement</th><th scope="col">Details</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>License Required</strong></td><td>Maine OCP Adult-Use Retail License</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Local Fee</strong></td><td>$3,000 annually</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>School Buffer</strong></td><td>500 ft minimum</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Commercial Rent</strong></td><td>$14-20/sq ft annually</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Current Dispensaries</strong></td><td>5-7 (approaching saturation)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Lewiston?</h2>
      <p>Lewiston is Maine's second-largest city (36,000 residents) with a growing cannabis market. Combined with Auburn across the Androscoggin River, the Lewiston-Auburn metro area offers 60,000+ potential customers.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Strength in Heritage" type="passion">
      Lewiston's deep roots and industrial spirit make it a resilient and loyal market. By honoring the city's heritage while bringing a modern cannabis experience, you can build a business that truly belongs. It's all about community connection here!
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Lewiston Market Data</h2>
      <table aria-label="Lewiston dispensary market data" caption="Market demographics and competitive landscape for Lewiston Maine dispensary opportunity">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>City Population</td><td>36,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>L-A Metro</td><td>60,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Primary Industries</td><td>Healthcare, Manufacturing, Retail</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Moderate-High</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Median Income</td><td>$48,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local X-Factor: The Franco-American Base</h2>
      <p><strong>What sets Lewiston apart:</strong> Lewiston has a strong Franco-American (French-Canadian) heritage with deep family roots and community loyalty. Word-of-mouth recommendations carry tremendous weight here.</p>
      <p><strong>Strategic Implication:</strong> Community-focused marketing and building genuine local relationships are essential. Operators who invest in the community reap long-term loyalty.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>State license required</strong> — OCP Adult-Use Retail</li>
        <li><strong>Local fee</strong> — Approximately $3,000 annually</li>
        <li><strong>Zoning</strong> — Commercial zones only</li>
        <li><strong>Distance</strong> — 500 ft from schools</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations</h2>
      <table aria-label="Lewiston recommended dispensary locations" caption="Recommended areas and rent benchmarks for Lewiston dispensary locations">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Area</th><th>Pros</th><th>Rent/Sq Ft</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Center Street</strong></td><td>Downtown, high traffic</td><td>$16-20</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong> Lisbon Street</strong></td><td>Main commercial corridor</td><td>$14-18</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Route 196</strong></td><td>Suburban, easier parking</td><td>$12-16</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Nearby Opportunities</h2>
      <p>The Lewiston-Auburn metro is Maine's second-largest market. Explore opportunities in nearby cities.</p>
      <table aria-label="Nearby dispensary guide opportunities">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>City</th><th>Distance</th><th>Guide</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Auburn</td><td>3 miles</td><td><a href="/guides/auburn-dispensary-guide/">Auburn Guide →</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Brunswick</td><td>20 miles</td><td><a href="/guides/brunswick-dispensary-guide/">Brunswick Guide →</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Portland</td><td>35 miles</td><td><a href="/guides/portland-dispensary-guide/">Portland Guide →</a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>✅ Opportunity:</strong> Second-largest Maine market</li>
        <li><strong>⚠️ Challenge:</strong> Approaching saturation</li>
        <li><strong>💰 Investment:</strong> $350K-450K startup</li>
        <li><strong>🔑 Strategy:</strong> Community loyalty is key</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine OCP</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">License Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">Real Estate Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>Informational only.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: #1a1a1a; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>